Example 4

If $U = \{-3, -2, -1, 0, 1, 2, 3\}$, $A = \{-2, 0, 2, 3\}$ and $B = \{-3, -2, 1, 3\}$:
(a) list: (i) $A'$ (ii) $B'$ (iii) $A \cap B$ (iv) $A \cup B$ (v) $A \cap B'$ (vi) $A' \cup B'$
(b) find $n(A' \cup B')$.

Solutions:

(a) (i) $A' = \{-3, -1, 1\}$ {all elements of $A$ not in $U$}
(ii) $B' = \{-1, 0, 2\}$ {all elements of $B$ not in $U$}
(iii) $A \cap B = \{-2, 3\}$ {all elements common to $A$ and $B$}
(iv) $A \cup B = \{-3, -2, 0, 1, 2, 3\}$ {all elements in $A$ or $B$ or both}
(v) $A \cap B' = \{-2, 0, 2, 3\} \cap \{-1, 0, 2\} = \{0, 2\}$
(vi) $A' \cup B' = \{-3, -1, 1\} \cup \{-1, 0, 2\} = \{-3, -1, 0, 1, 2\}$

(b) $n(A' \cup B') = 5$ {as there are 5 members in this set}
